name: CIA World Factbook
comment: The CIA's large public information dataset containing many key statistics on the countries of the world. Downloaded from cia.gov, then extracted some data into a SQL table and exported as CSV. Last updated 2007-06-19

name: opengeodb.sf.net
comment: Open database of cities and zip codes of the german speaking area in Europe: Germany, Austria, Switzerland, Belgium and Liechtenstein

name: Countries of the World
comment: Taken from MySQL's world sample database (its a bit out-of-date). Originally taken from Statistics Finland: World in Figures

name: Largest Cities of the World
comment: Also taken from MySQL's world sample database, less out-of-date.

name: ISO-3166
comment: ISO Standard 3166 defines three-part geographic codes for names of countries, dependent areas and principal subdevisions thereof. This is a partial listing of its entries.

name: Cities with population > 15000
comment: Imported from geonames.org. Removed a few columns to make the tables more readable.

name: Cities in China
comment: Also imported from geonames.org - Country code CN - China

name: Cities in Germany
comment: Also imported from geonames.org - Country code DE - Germany

name: Cities in Russia
comment: Also imported from geonames.org - Country code RU - Russia

name: Cities in United States
comment: Also imported from geonames.org - Country code US - United States
